THE Premier Soccer League (PSL) has distanced itself from the decision to take the Telkom Knockout final to the smaller Princess Magogo Stadium, insisting the sponsors had the final say. Saturday will see Bidvest Wits and Bloemfontein Celtic battle it out in the Knockout final at the 12 000-seater stadium in KwaMashu at 6pm.Explaining the rationale behind taking the final to the KwaMashu venue, PSL CEO Mato Madlala said the last four teams – Kaizer Chiefs, Wits, Celtic and Polokwane City – were consulted before the final decision was taken on where the final should be played. It is a league rule to play the final at a neutral venue.if(typeof za24_DisplayAd != "undefined") za24_DisplayAd("300x250","2");var viewReq = new Array();function vu(u) {var i=new Image();i.src=u.replace("&amp;","&");viewReq.push(i);}vu("https://securepubads.g.doubleclick.net/pcs/view?xai\x3dAKAOjstGphj0MeMNi9yOaZNypB0rZxQOCyTfuyaPBQhytlvSVYWj5FNc8qBEkMnIDpyNfzIRWdLc1ILN2-z0g0zcy-2jj24t1KrRD-AvzLjqACpw0LbuI1T8HcLpzkk_g6BRhQp3JEuC59yAZcF8XhzQ2YlRv7pIOfzKDc86FJjhTS-nuuJwVONThT2sFO1WJz6hDeS_N1MooHJ7koSOsF5tEhmJye0fJ0bdi4FC9dXgBO28bGjLiyo1pWxLRY-CMbi0Baoz9SCUTzGHo1DzR6v-\x26sig\x3dCg0ArKJSzDQ4Q3BuVGDzEAE\x26urlfix\x3d1\x26adurl\x3d")

   
